Uttar Pradesh
Nov 06, 2014
Murder, Dowry Harassment
Description:
			A man has been sentenced to seven years rigorous imprisonment by a court here for killing his wife for dowry four years ago.

Additional District Sessions Judge D P N Singh also imposed a fine of Rs 10,000 on the convict, Ritesh, yesterday.

In August 2010, the victim, Pushpa, who had married Ritesh just two months back, was found strangulated to death in Charawa village in Bheempura area, prosecution sources said.

She had also been attacked with a sharp-edged weapon.

Pushpa's father Kapoor Chandra had alleged that Ritesh had been harassing her for dowry since their marriage.


